  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Building inspector (Facility)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope :</strong></p><p>The Contractor is required to carry out inspection of properties including returned properties and all follow-up actions to monitor and report compliance with requirements provided by Client and that the premises do not infringe authorities’ requirements, including but not limited to:</p><ol><li>Non-compliance to statutory requirements, e.g.</li><li>Unapproved building works and any additions/alterations,</li><li>Fire Safety Hazards,</li><li>Unapproved usage or change of usage of premises,</li><li>Illegal activities in premises e.g. illegal dumping, gambling, etc,</li><li>Unapproved worker’s dormitory;</li><li>Unapproved sales of diesel;</li><li>Unapproved subletting;</li><li>Encroachment;</li><li>Poor Maintenance/Housekeeping</li><li>Unauthorized reclamation.</li><li>The Works also include verification of gross floor area (GFA) and monitoring the reinstatement works of the return properties to Clients satisfaction.</li></ol><p>The works of the Contractor shall include:-</p><ol><li>Make arrangement with companies and carry out inspection of their premises;</li><li>Identify issues and raise concerns relating to non-compliance with statutory and Client requirements; and</li><li>Follow up with reinstatement works for return properties and rectification of breaches for all properties.</li></ol><p><br /><strong>Work Requirement :</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Real Estate or Facilities Management preferably</li><li>Certified as a Fire Safety Manager</li><li>Monday to Friday : 8.00 AM to 6.00 PM </li><li><strong>Must have own transport* </strong></li></ul>",
